New story time!

Journey of a Lifetime

https://archiveofourown.org/works/42612735

>Intro
Cade Givellia is a man on a mission. Tasked with the delivery of an important package in the dead of winter, he journeys out to a new city to complete his duties. Once he arrives, instead of simply making his delivery to the Greystar family and returning home, he finds himself graciously welcomed into the unfamiliar family's manor, housing him for the cold winter night and treating him like one of their own. But little does he know, one of the house's residents will make him more than just a mere guest.

Wanted to challenge myself and write a full story in just one week. It was tough, but I think the outcome was pretty good. Feedback always welcome, of course

Sweetheart Deal: Chapter Nineteen - Evasions

Welcome to Nuevo Carcangel, circa 2174. A century has passed since a plague killed half of humanity. No one living now knows why some of the survivors are called chimeras, nor how the plague created them - if it did.
Christina Marlowe, a private investigator and a fox-type chimera, has other concerns. She's living in one of the biggest city-states. What technology used to exist is gone. She knows the trains and streetcars, her trusty revolver, and that she needs a big case.
Nathaniel Berrymount may be it. He's nervous at first and rightly so. The signs point to a sweetheart deal that's meant to collapse, leaving the victor with everything.
Marlowe will have to think and talk fast as events pile up. A Boss wants his blueprints back. What do the buns of The Warren want? And can she keep her client from falling for her?

In this chapter, Marlowe does a thing she's an expert at: walking into somewhere and pushing people around. It's the start of another long day sniffing out the truth. The person paying for it all is going to learn all about vixies by the end of it and might regret getting out of bed today.
Then again, so might Marlowe.

Coming soon - Chapter Twenty: Building Plans
Thank you for your time and for reading.
